race.comment: PHAROAH'S DAUGHTER (8) had been racing well before an explosive five-length win last start over this distance at Kilmore in a BM56. Meets some better types this time but the manner of that last win cannot be ignored. STREET LARK (7) has been well found in betting at all three runs this prep but has failed to deliver. Obviously has more to offer and the addition of blinkers for the first time today made spark a revival. MISS CASTELVECCHIO (6) settled worse than midfield then warmed to the task late to get up for fourth when resuming over 1454m at Kyneton recently. Fitter and on a bigger track out to this distance makes plenty of appeal. FINALE (3) mixes her form but from the inside draw she gets the perfect run and should be hard to stop when presented. ZAAFFAIR STEAL (11) made late ground when resuming at Mornington last time. Nicely placed over this slightly longer journey second-up.
